-- Reserve Bank's Stevens Says Rate Setting Appropriate for `Period Ahead'
-- B y   V i c t o r i a   B a t c h e l o r
-- 2010-11-25T22:35:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-25/reserve-bank-s-stevens-says-rate-setting-appropriate-for-period-ahead-.html
The Reserve Bank of Australia’s
rate setting is appropriate for the “period ahead,” Governor
Glenn Stevens told the House of Representatives Economics
Committee in Canberra today.  Recent rate decisions have been finely balanced, Stevens
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
